EmailTemplate.description: New Airline wiling to join its 1st BSP - Request for requirements
EmailTemplate.name: New Airline Join 1st BSP
EmailTemplate.subject: Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber} - {!Case.Subject}
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Contact.Name},
Please find below a summary of the costs and eligibility requirements to join BSP.
Cost:
The costs related to the participation in a BSP can be found in the attached ,BSP Price List for 2013. Please refer to the applicable country {!Case.Country__c}. Kindly note that these are the main costs your Airline needs to consider:
- BSP Joining Fees (onetime fee): {!Case.Country__c}
- BSP Transaction (SCU) fees - this is the fee charged by IATA for every transaction processed by the BSP for your Airline. It is invoiced monthly. The SCU fee for {!Case.Country__c} is USD (Insert amount)
- BSP Products and services - these will be charged according to the products and services that you select (details attached) and are invoiced monthly.
- Central & Regional Management fees - these are calculated by IATA based on the number of BSPs where the Airline participates and the transactions processed. These are invoiced monthly.
- Non IATA airlines will be charged with 500 USD annually per BSP where they participate.
Eligibility and Requirements:
Please note that in order for your Airline to participate in the BSP, an IATA Designator and Accounting code is required. In the case you do not hold these, please contact airlinecoding@iata.org.
Your Airline needs to be a scheduled Airline and able to issue Electronic Tickets as per governing IATA resolutions.
Documents and Agreements:
Please find herewith a summary of the documentation that you will need to complete, sign and present to IATA:
Counterindemnity Agreement (Reso 850, Attachment C): to be signed once only for all BSPs (template attached) Form of Concurrence (FoC, Reso 850 Att E) - for carriers which are not Members of IATA, to be signed once only for all BSPs (template attached)
The above mentioned forms must state the Legal Name of the Airline as well as their IATA Designator and Numeric (accounting) Code. The address must be that of the Airline’s Head Office. Two originals should be completed and signed by the Airline's Senior Management, either Chief Executive Officer, Chief Financial Office or Director General. The originals are to be sent to IATA Geneva for countersignature.
3) Form of Application by Non-IATA Air Carrier (850 Att D), to be signed for each BSP a Non-IATA Carrier wishes to participate in. Once signed by the Airline it should be sent to
IATA Geneva. With this form note a copy of your current timetable is required. Template attached.
4) Letter issued by your E-Ticketing System Provider confirming your Airline is ready to issue ETKT's as per IATA Resolutions
5) IATA BSP Participation Joining Form (attached) - to be completed, signed and stamped by your Airline. The original needs to be sent to IATA Geneva.
6) In order for IATA to settle the proceedings of the BSP sales to your Airline, you need to present a Bank Account Mandate. The possible options are IATA Currency Clearance System for cross border settlements (www.iata.org/iccs) or a Bank Mandate indicating a bank account in the BSP Country and currency.
7) In case there are any local requirements for BSP participation in {!Case.Country__c}, please find attached the additional documentation requirements. . For more information you may contact log a new query through our IATA Customer Portal mentioning the referemce case number.
Please do not hesitate to contact us in case of any further queries/assistance that may be required with regards to the above. Our team will be glad to assist you accordingly.
For future support in regards to any other query, please log a new inquiry through our customer portal at http://www.iata.org/customer-portal/Pages/contactus.aspx
We look forward to hearing from you shortly.
Thank you,
{!Case.OwnerFullName}
Global Airline Participation Team
Financial and Distribution Services
